- 'golden price range' is a metaphor for sale prices between $200,000 and $500,000;
- 'shadows of crime' metaphorically describe crime rates;
- 'gleam of tax burdens' refers to average property tax rates;
- 'prism of safety and fiscal weight' represents sorting by crime rate (ascending) and average property tax rate (descending).
